{"word":"εὔφρων","slug":"εὔφρων","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>εὔφρων</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:φρήν'><el>φρήν</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>cheerful, gladsome, merry</i>, of persons making merry, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>: <a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <a href='S:εὐφρόνως'><el>εὐφρόνως</el></a>, <i>with good cheer</i>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> <i>cheering, making glad</i> or <i>merry</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>later, <i>well-minded, favourable, gracious</i>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—<a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a>, in this sense, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b>= <a href='S:εὔφημος'><el>εὔφημος</el></a>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}